article.headline: (2) SAINT JOSEPHS 71, (8) RUTGERS 62
article.story: PISCATAWAY, N.J. (AP) -- Marquis Webb scored 14 points to lead Rutgers to a 64-41 exhibition victory over Caldwell on Wednesday night in Fred Hill's first game as the Scarlet Knights' coach. J.R. Inman and Anthony Farmer each added nine points for Rutgers, and Ollie Bailey had eight rebounds. B.J. Suchy led the Division II Cougars with a 15 points. The Scarlet Knights open their regular season Nov. 15 at home against Kansas State.
